FBIS3-49726 "dreeu010_y_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-010 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Jan 1994 YUGOSLAVIA Federal Defense Council Holds Session, Issues Statement LD1301150494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 1216 GMT 13 Jan 94 LD1301150494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] Belgrade, 13 Jan (TANJUG) -- A session of the Supreme Defense Council was held in Belgrade today under the chairmanship of FRY President Zoran Lilic, the Yugoslav president's military office has announced. In addition to members of the Supreme Defense Council -- Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic and Montenegrin President Momir Bulatovic -- the session was also attended by Yugoslav Prime Minister Radoje Kontic, Federal Defense Minister Pavle Bulatovic, and Lieutenant Colonel General Momcilo pereisic, the Yugoslav Army chief of the general staff. The Supreme Defense Council discussed the financing of the Yugoslav Army and concluded that in 1994 priority should be given to securing the necessary financial resources to maintain the necessary level of combat readiness, and to improve the living standards of Yugoslav Army members, a statement by the Yugoslav president's military office says.
